 100:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_ENABLE:      Enable the SMBUS peripheral
 101:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_DISABLE:     Disable the SMBUS peripheral
 102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_GET_FLAG:    Check whether the specified SMBUS flag is set or not
 103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_CLEAR_FLAG:  Clear the specified SMBUS pending flag
 104:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_ENABLE_IT:   Enable the specified SMBUS interrupt
 105:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****       (+) __HAL_SMBUS_DISABLE_IT:  Disable the specified SMBUS interrupt
 106:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c **** 
 107:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      *** Callback registration ***
 108:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      =============================================
 109:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 110:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      The compilation flag USE_HAL_SMBUS_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 111:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 112:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Use Functions HAL_SMBUS_RegisterCallback() or HAL_SMBUS_RegisterAddrCallback()
 113:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      to register an interrupt callback.
 114:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 115:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Function HAL_SMBUS_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 116:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 117:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 118:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 119:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 120:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 121:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 122:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 123:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 124:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 125:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 126:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 127:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      For specific callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : HAL_SMBUS_RegisterAddrCa
 128:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 129:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Use function HAL_SMBUS_UnRegisterCallback to reset a callback to the default
 130:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      weak function.
 131:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      HAL_SMBUS_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 132:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      and the Callback ID.
 133:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 134:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 135:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 136:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 137:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 138:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 139:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 140:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 141:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 142:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 143:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      For callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : HAL_SMBUS_UnRegisterAddrCallback.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Xuleo\AppData\Local\Temp\cc9Utr5M.s 			page 4


 144:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 145:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      By default, after the HAL_SMBUS_Init() and when the state is HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET
 146:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 147:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      examples HAL_SMBUS_MasterTxCpltCallback(), HAL_SMBUS_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 148:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 149:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_SMBUS_Init()/ HAL_SMBUS_DeInit() only when
 150:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 151:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_SMBUS_Init()/ HAL_SMBUS_DeInit()
 152:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 153:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****     [..]
 154:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_I2C_STATE_READY state only.
 155:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 156:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      in HAL_I2C_STATE_READY or HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET state,
 157:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_smbus.c ****      thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
